# Implementation Plan - Visual Overhaul

This plan outlines the steps to apply the "Cyber Slate" design theme, allowing for a premium feel without altering backend logic.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **No new packages**: We will stick to `Bootstrap Icons` (already present) but style them to look more modern.
> **Assumptions**: The [Sidebar](file:///e:/IC-UFF/tcc-nvr-frontend/src/app/layout/sidebar/sidebar.component.ts#5-94), [Topbar](file:///e:/IC-UFF/tcc-nvr-frontend/src/app/layout/topbar/topbar.component.ts#4-137), and [CameraList](file:///e:/IC-UFF/tcc-nvr-frontend/src/app/camera-list/camera-list.ts#7-49) are the primary targets for now.

## Proposed Changes

### Global Styles
#### [MODIFY] [styles.css](file:///e:/IC-UFF/tcc-nvr-frontend/src/styles.css)
- Replace color variables with the **Slate Palette** (bg-dark: #0f172a, bg-surface: #1e293b).
- Add utility classes for `glass-panel` (backdrop-filter) and `glow-text`.
- Update scrollbar styling to be slimmer and darker.

### Layout Components
#### [MODIFY] [sidebar.component.ts](file:///e:/IC-UFF/tcc-nvr-frontend/src/app/layout/sidebar/sidebar.component.ts)
- Update CSS to use `glass-panel`.
- Improve navigation items spacing and hover effects (active state with glow).
- Change logo area to look more branded.

#### [MODIFY] [topbar.component.ts](file:///e:/IC-UFF/tcc-nvr-frontend/src/app/layout/topbar/topbar.component.ts)
- Apply glassmorphism.
- Style the "Panic" button to be a "Pulse" button.
- Clean up the clock/date typography (JetBrains Mono for numbers).

### Camera Management
#### [MODIFY] [camera-list.ts / html / css](file:///e:/IC-UFF/tcc-nvr-frontend/src/app/camera-list/camera-list.ts)
- **Major Change**: Convert from `<ul>` list to a **CSS Grid of Cards**.
- Each card will show:
    - Placeholder Image / Icon
    - Camera Name (Bold)
    - IP/URL (Truncated, Monospace)
    - Status Indicator (Green/Red dot)
    - Action Buttons Row (Icons only, tooltips on hover)

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- **Visual Check**: Run the app and verify:
    - Dark blue/slate theme is applied globally.
    - Sidebar/Topbar have the "frosted glass" effect.
    - Camera List appears as a responsive grid of cards.
    - Hover states feel smooth (transitions).
